    PROCEDURE assignOptionText@1000000052(ptxtOption@1000000000 : Text;pbFlag@1000000001 : Boolean) returnText : Text;
    BEGIN
      CASE ptxtOption OF
        '':
            returnText := '';
        'Biohazard':
          IF pbFlag THEN
            returnText := tcBio
          ELSE
            returnText := tcBioLong;
        'Corrosion':
          IF pbFlag THEN
            returnText := tcCorrosion
          ELSE
            returnText := tcCorrosionLong;
        'Environment':
          IF pbFlag THEN
            returnText := tcEnviro
          ELSE
            returnText := tcEnviroLong;
        'Exclamation Mark':
          IF pbFlag THEN
            returnText := tcExclamation
          ELSE
            returnText := tcExclamationLong;
        'Explosion':
          IF pbFlag THEN
            returnText := tcExplode
          ELSE
            returnText := tcExplodeLong;
        'Flame':
          IF pbFlag THEN
            returnText := tcFlame
          ELSE
            returnText := tcFlameLong;
        'Oxidizer':
          IF pbFlag THEN
            returnText := tcFlameCircle
          ELSE
            returnText := tcFlameCircleLong;
        'Gas':
          IF pbFlag THEN
            returnText := tcGas
          ELSE
            returnText := tcGasLong;
        'Health Hazard':
          IF pbFlag THEN
            returnText := tcHealth
          ELSE
            returnText := tcHealthLong;
        'Skull and Crossbones':
          IF pbFlag THEN
            returnText := tcSkull
          ELSE
            returnText := tcSkullLong;
      END;
    END;

    PROCEDURE addLedgerItemLabel@1000000016(precItemLedgerEntry@1000000000 : Record 32);
    BEGIN
      //Function to add Item Ledger Entry and Item Tracking information

      //Checks for duplicates.  Also, if the base item function was called, then no more items will be
      // added and only one label will be printed.
      trecItemTracingBuffer.RESET;
      trecItemTracingBuffer.SETRANGE("Item No.", precItemLedgerEntry."Item No.");
      trecItemTracingBuffer.SETRANGE("Lot No.", precItemLedgerEntry."Lot No.");
      trecItemTracingBuffer.SETRANGE("Serial No.", precItemLedgerEntry."Serial No.");
      IF trecItemTracingBuffer.FINDFIRST THEN
        EXIT;

      //If it makes it here don't want to have labels that do not also show the item tracking info
      // so take the first 'base' label that would have been inserted since there was no filters set
      // on the request page, and change that to a label with the first set of item tracking info.
      trecItemTracingBuffer.RESET;
      trecItemTracingBuffer.SETRANGE("Item No.", precItemLedgerEntry."Item No.");
      trecItemTracingBuffer.SETFILTER("Lot No.", '%1','');
      trecItemTracingBuffer.SETFILTER("Serial No.", '%1','');
      IF trecItemTracingBuffer.FINDFIRST THEN BEGIN
        IF precItemLedgerEntry."Serial No." <> '' THEN BEGIN
          trecItemTracingBuffer."Lot No." := precItemLedgerEntry."Serial No.";
          trecItemTracingBuffer.Open := FALSE;
        END
        ELSE BEGIN
          trecItemTracingBuffer."Lot No." := precItemLedgerEntry."Lot No.";
          trecItemTracingBuffer.Open := TRUE;
        END;
        trecItemTracingBuffer.MODIFY;
      END
      //Continue with the rest of the item ledger entries
      ELSE BEGIN
        trecItemTracingBuffer.INIT;
        IF precItemLedgerEntry."Serial No." <> '' THEN BEGIN
          trecItemTracingBuffer."Lot No." := precItemLedgerEntry."Serial No.";
          trecItemTracingBuffer.Open := FALSE;
        END
        ELSE BEGIN
          trecItemTracingBuffer."Lot No." := precItemLedgerEntry."Lot No.";
          trecItemTracingBuffer.Open := TRUE;
        END;
        trecItemTracingBuffer."Item No." := precItemLedgerEntry."Item No.";
        recItem.SETRANGE("No.", precItemLedgerEntry."Item No.");
        IF recItem.FINDFIRST THEN BEGIN
          trecItemTracingBuffer."Item Description" := recItem.Description;
          //Using fields with the same data types for storing values
          // 2018-::begin
          trecItemTracingBuffer."Location Code" := recItem."Product Group Code";
          // 2018-::end
          trecItemTracingBuffer."Variant Code" := recItem."Special Equipment Code";
          trecItemTracingBuffer.Quantity := recItem."Net Weight";
        END
        ELSE
          trecItemTracingBuffer."Item Description" := 'N/A';
        trecItemTracingBuffer."Line No." := iCount;
        trecItemTracingBuffer.INSERT;
        iCount := iCount + 1;
      END;
    END;

    PROCEDURE addBaseItemLabel@1000000021(precItem@1000000000 : Record 27);
    BEGIN
      //Function to only add information not related to item tracking

      trecItemTracingBuffer.SETRANGE("Item No.", precItem."No.");
      trecItemTracingBuffer.INIT;
      trecItemTracingBuffer."Item No." := precItem."No.";
      trecItemTracingBuffer."Item Description" := precItem.Description;
      trecItemTracingBuffer.Open := TRUE;
      //Using fields with the same data types for storing values
      // 2018-::begin
      trecItemTracingBuffer."Location Code" := recItem."Product Group Code";
      // 2018-::end
      trecItemTracingBuffer."Variant Code" := recItem."Special Equipment Code";
      trecItemTracingBuffer.Quantity := recItem."Net Weight";
      trecItemTracingBuffer."Line No." := iCount;
      trecItemTracingBuffer.INSERT;
      iCount := iCount + 1;
    END;

  <Code>Public Function BlankZero(ByVal Value As Decimal)
    if Value = 0 then
        Return ""
    end if
    Return Value
End Function

Public Function BlankPos(ByVal Value As Decimal)
    if Value &gt; 0 then
        Return ""
    end if
    Return Value
End Function

Public Function BlankZeroAndPos(ByVal Value As Decimal)
    if Value &gt;= 0 then
        Return ""
    end if
    Return Value
End Function

Public Function BlankNeg(ByVal Value As Decimal)
    if Value &lt; 0 then
        Return ""
    end if
    Return Value
End Function

Public Function BlankNegAndZero(ByVal Value As Decimal)
    if Value &lt;= 0 then
        Return ""
    end if
    Return Value
End Function
